title: Sculptor's Model
description:
Sculptor’s model of limestone. One side has in raised relief, a male head with no headdress; a falcon wearing the double crown; an uraeus and on the lower register two bird hieroglyphs and an unknown object. The reverse has a splendid example also in raised relief of a high intef headdress with a detail from it scratched crudely beside it. 
Condition: Edges chipped.
credit_line: Gift of Evangeline Wilbour Blashfield, Theodora Wilbour, and Victor Wilbour honoring the wishes of their mother, Charlotte Beebe Wilbour, as a memorial to their father, Charles Edwin Wilbour
